-- Venezuela’s Chavez Had Tumor Removed, Says No Metastasis
-- B y   C o r i n a   R o d r i g u e z   P o n s   a n d   J o s e   O r o z c o
-- 2012-03-04T17:26:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-04/venezuela-s-chavez-had-tumor-removed-says-no-metastasis.html
Venezuelan President  Hugo Chavez ,
speaking on state television, said doctors removed a cancerous
tumor on Feb. 26 and that there was no sign that the cancer had
spread.  Chavez said he will undergo radiotherapy in coming weeks
and doesn’t rule out other treatment options for his undisclosed
cancer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Corina Pons in Caracas at 
 crpons@bloomberg.net ;
